This paper deals with the problem of exploring a ring using mobile robots, which is a classic problem in robotics and distributed computing. The paper focuses on the deterministic setting, which is a subfield of robotics (cs.RO) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also involves the study of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) for exploring the ring, as well as the use of mathematical analysis (cs.MA) to prove the optimality of the proposed algorithm. Finally, the paper presents a protocol for coordinating the robots, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY).
